"'''The Trouble with Squibs'''" was a short story written by [[Troy Denning]], originally published in [[Star Wars Insider 67|''Star Wars Insider'' 67]] and later archived on [[Hyperspace: The Official Star Wars Fan Club|Hyperspace]].

==Plot summary==
On a trip to [[Pavo Prime/Legends|Pavo Prime]] to retrieve [[Alderaan/Legends|Alderaanian]] [[boasa]] statues, [[Han Solo/Legends|Han]] and [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa Solo]] run into two old "friends": the [[Squib/Legends|Squibs]] [[Emala]] and [[Sligh]], who they met on [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]] while trying to obtain the [[Moss painting/Legends|moss painting]] ''[[Killik Twilight]]''. However, the third Squib, [[Grees]], was conspicuously absent. It turned out that Grees had been frozen in [[Carbonite/Legends|carbonite]] and was in the possession of a [[Jenet/Legends|Jenet]] casino owner on Pavo Prime. Han and Leia helped the Squibs rescue Grees, and obtained the boasa statues, but they were fed misinformation by the Squibs about a new [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] technology.

